race.description: South Coast Buccaneers Afl Masters 2026 Handicap (C1)
race.comment: BOMBAY BOOM (1) sat on the speed but couldn't hold on as an odds-on fave at Orange last start in tougher company, but he didn't lose any admirers. The form out of that race has been solid and he has the speed to get across from the draw. Heywood hops back in the saddle now and he can continue to work through the grades. LIGHTLY SPARKLED (6) comes here third-up and ready to peak after going under as the favourite at Gundagai most recently. Gets the blinkers on third-up today and maps to get every chance for Martin. Can put her best foot forward. GIRLS WEEKEND (2) is another who lands here third-up and with the blinkers going on for the first time. She has plenty of speed and she'll need it to get across from the draw. Form out of her last start has already been franked and she won't be far away. NEFRADITE (8) creates plenty of interest after an impressive last start win. ROYAL MEMORY (7) is worth including on the back of a recent trial win.
